I"â#<p><strong>Wax</strong> is a <a href="http://go-dh.github.io/mincomp/">minimal computing</a> project for producing digital exhibitions focused on longevity, low costs, and flexibility. Our underlying technology is made to learn and to teach, and can produce beautifully rendered, high-quality image collections and scholarly exhibits. To start using Wax, please see our <a href="https://minicomp.github.io/wiki/#/wax/">documentation</a> for installation instructions and more.</p>

<p>The collection items in this demo are from The Museum of Islamic Art, Qatar, (courtesy of <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Google_Art_Project_works_in_The_Museum_of_Islamic_Art,_Qatar">WikiMedia</a> and <a href="https://www.google.com/culturalinstitute/about/artproject/">Google Art Project</a>) and The Qatar National Library (via <a href="https://www.wdl.org/en/">World Digital Library</a>).</p>

